org.apache.beam.sdk.values

Interface POutput

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    PCollectionView<T>, PValue
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    PCollection, PCollectionList, PCollectionTuple, PCollectionViews.IterablePCollectionView, PCollectionViews.ListPCollectionView, PCollectionViews.MapPCollectionView, PCollectionViews.MultimapPCollectionView, PCollectionViews.SingletonPCollectionView, PDone, POutputValueBase, PValueBase, TypedPValue

    public interface POutput
    The interface for things that might be output from a PTransform.

    • Method Detail

      • getPipeline

        Pipeline getPipeline()
        Returns the owning Pipeline of this POutput.

      • expand

        List<TaggedPValue> expand()
        Expands this POutput into a list of its component output PValues.
        • A PValue expands to itself.
        • A tuple or list of PValues (such as PCollectionTuple or PCollectionList) expands to its component PValue PValues.

        Not intended to be invoked directly by user code.

      • recordAsOutput

        void recordAsOutput(AppliedPTransform<?,?,?> transform)
        Records that this POutput is an output of the given PTransform.

        For a compound POutput, it is advised to call this method on each component POutput.

        This is not intended to be invoked by user code, but is automatically invoked as part of applying the producing PTransform.

      • finishSpecifyingOutput

        @Deprecated
void finishSpecifyingOutput(PInput input,
                                        PTransform<?,?> transform)
        Deprecated. see BEAM-1199
        As part of applying the producing PTransform, finalizes this output to make it ready for being used as an input and for running.

        This includes ensuring that all PCollections have Coders specified or defaulted.

        Automatically invoked whenever this POutput is output, after finishSpecifyingOutput(PInput, PTransform) has been called on each component PValue returned by expand().
